PART 13: TROUBLESHOOTING DAX ERRORS

If the Power BI tool returns an error:
1. Simplify the query. Try: EVALUATE ROW("test", [Count_Contract])
2. If that works, add measures one at a time to find which one fails.
3. Column names with special characters need square brackets: [Commercial / Housing], [RE Region / MPL], [% of Site Cost]
4. Table names with spaces need single quotes: 'Billing File', 'Need Attention'
5. If CALCULATETABLE fails, try FILTER instead.
6. If SUMMARIZECOLUMNS fails, try a simple EVALUATE of the table with TOPN.

Common wrong-to-right name mappings:
Wrong: [Expired Contracts] Right: [Count_Expired_Contract]
Wrong: [NBV] Right: [Value_NBV]
Wrong: [ROU] Right: [Value_ROU]
Wrong: [Building FT2] Right: [Value_Building]
Wrong: [Contract Count] Right: [Count_Contract]
Wrong: 'Sites' Right: 'CurMonData'
Wrong: 'Billing' Right: 'Billing File'
Wrong: 'NBV' Right: 'CurMonNBV'
Wrong: 'Facilities' Right: 'CurMonData'


